    "read": "The TileLang dKV body is not the whole sparse-MLA backward wall. At the layer-2 S4096 route, compressed TileLang is 10.4 ms median, but the full shared-KV backward boundary is 37.5 ms median before considering profile overhead and compile outliers. The next useful sparse branch remains whole-boundary fusion consuming q, dO, compressed/shared KV, LI indices, output, lse/sink directly, eliminating gather_selected_kv/probs/grad_logits/local scatter materialization instead of only replacing the late compressed dKV sink.",
